description: POK√âMON Detective Pikachu - In Theaters May 10, 2019http://www.detectivepikachumovie.com/https://www.facebook.com/detectivepikachumovie/https://twitter.com/DetPikachuMovie https://www.instagram.com/detectivepikachumovie/The world of Pok√©mon comes to life!The first-ever live-action Pok√©mon movie, ‚ÄúPOK√âMON Detective Pikachu‚Äù stars Ryan Reynolds as the titular character in the first-ever live-action movie based on the iconic face of the global Pok√©mon brand‚Äîone of the world‚Äôs most popular, multi-generation entertainment properties and most successful media franchises of all time.Fans everywhere can now experience Pikachu on the big screen as never before, as a talking detective Pikachu, a Pok√©mon like no other. The film also showcases a wide array of beloved Pok√©mon characters, each with its own unique abilities and personality.The story begins when ace private eye Harry Goodman goes mysteriously missing, prompting his 21-year-old son Tim to find out what happened. Aiding in the investigation is Harry‚Äôs former Pok√©mon partner, Detective Pikachu: a hilariously wise-cracking, adorable super-sleuth who is a puzzlement even to himself. Finding that they are uniquely equipped to communicate with one another, Tim and Pikachu join forces on a thrilling adventure to unravel the tangled mystery. Chasing clues together through the neon-lit streets of Ryme City‚Äîa sprawling, modern metropolis where humans and Pok√©mon live side by side in a hyper-realistic live-action world‚Äîthey encounter a diverse cast of Pok√©mon characters and uncover a shocking plot that could destroy this peaceful co-existence and threaten the whole Pok√©mon universe.‚ÄúPOK√âMON Detective Pikachu‚Äù also stars Justice Smith (‚ÄúJurassic World: Fallen Kingdom‚Äù) as Tim; Kathryn Newton (‚ÄúLady Bird,‚Äù TV‚Äôs ‚ÄúBig Little Lies‚Äù) as Lucy, a junior reporter following her first big story; and Oscar nominee Ken Watanabe (‚ÄúGodzilla,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Last Samurai‚Äù) as Lt. Aliens‚Äù), the ‚ÄúPOK√âMON Detective Pikachu‚Äù creative filmmaking team includes two-time Oscar nominated director of photography John Mathieson (‚ÄúThe Phantom of the Opera,‚Äù ‚ÄúGladiator‚Äù), production designer Nigel Phelps (‚ÄúPirates of the Caribbean: Dead Men Tell No Lies‚Äù) and Oscar-winning editor Mark Sanger (‚ÄúGravity‚Äù). description: Watch Why Samatha Says Naga Chaitanya Is My Pet on the fifth episode of McDowell's No 1 Yaari With Rana Season 2. Episode 5 features Samantha Prabhu, Chinmayi Sriprada and Nandini Reddy Click here to download the Viu App to stay tuned for more - http://bit.ly/ViuApp-YT#McDowellsNo1YaariWithRana #Season2 #RanaDaggubatiSamantha worked part-time on modeling assignments. She soon received offers for film roles and made her acting debut in Gautham Menon's critically acclaimed Telugu romance film, Ye Maaya Chesave which fetched her the Filmfare Award for Best Debut Actress and a Nandi Award. Samantha then became the second actress ever to win both the Filmfare Award for Best Tamil Actress and the Filmfare Award for Best Telugu Actress in the same year, for her performances in the films Neethaane En Ponvasantham (2012) and Eega (2012). Since then, she has primarily opted to appear in the leading female role in hero-centric Telugu and Tamil films. Nandini Reddy was introduced to Gangaraju Gunnam through a mutual friend and in 1995 she worked on his children's movie Little Soldiers as an Assistant Director. After that film was released, cinematographer Rasool Ellore introduced her to Krishna Vamsi, who refused at the time to take her into his team.  Actress Ramya Krishnan then persuaded Vamsi to take her for his next project, Chandralekha. She became an integral part of Vamsi's team up to and including the filming of Shakti, a Hindi remake of Anthahpuram. Chinmayi participated and won the singing contest of Sun TV, Saptasawarangal, following which she was introduced by Singer Srinivas to film composer A. R. Rahman. Chinmayi's playback singing career began with her performance of Rahman's Oru Dheivam Thanta Poove for the film Kannathil Muthamittal. tags: karamkalla paratha,Cabbage Stuffed Paratha Recipe,how to make cabbage paratha,Cabbage Paratha Recipe with Step By Step Photos,patta gobhi paratha recipe,cabbage paratha without stuffing,cabbage paratha punjabi style,‡§™‡§§‡•ç‡§§‡§æ‡§ó‡•ã‡§≠‡•Ä ‡§∏‡•ç‡§ü‡§´‡•ç‡§° ‡§™‡§∞‡§æ‡§Ç‡§†‡§æ ‡§∞‡•á‡§∏‡§ø‡§™‡•Ä,cabbage paratha recipe in hindi,How to make Patta Gobhi Paratha,cabbage paratha for toddler
description: Cabbage Paratha Recipe, patta gobhi paratha recipe, band gobhi paratha recipe, Karamkalla Paratha,Ingredients:Cabbage - 300 gmsWheat flour - 2 cups (300 gms)Oil - 3 to 4 tbspGreen Coriander - 2 to 3 tbsp (finely chopped)Green chillies - 2 (finely chopped)Ginger paste - ¬Ω tspCumin seeds - ¬º tspCoriander powder - ¬Ω tspRed chilli powder - ¬º tspSalt - less than 1 tsp How to make stuffed Cabbage Paratha For the dough 1- Take 2 cups of wheat flour and add ¬Ω tsp of salt in it. 2- Add 2 tsp of Oil in it and mix them. 3- Add 1 cup of water in intervals and knead the soft dough for parathas.4- Cover and set it for 15-20 minutes.For the stuffing 1- Take 300 gms of cabbage, remove its upper 3-4 leaves and separate the rest of them individually.2- Add salt in the lukewarm water in a vessel. 3- Dip the cabbage leaves in it for 10 minutes. 4- Drain them out and wash with fresh water in a strainer so that the extra water moves out of it. 5- Keep them in basket and dry them until water disappears.6- Make a bunch of some leaves and chop them finely. 7- Preheat 2 tsp of Oil in a pan, add 2 tsp of cumin seeds in it and roast on the low flame.8-  Saute ¬Ω tsp of Ginger paste, 2 finely chopped Green chillies, ¬Ω tsp of coriander powder, ¬º tsp of Red chilli powder in it.9- Add chopped cabbage in the roasted spices, ¬Ω tsp of salt, stir and cook them for 2 minutes. 10- Add 2 to 3 tbsp of finely chopped coriander and cook it while stirring for 1 to 2 minutes. 11- The stuffing is ready and has cooked. For the paratha 1- After, 20 minutes mash the dough slightly and preheat the pan or parathas. ‚Äò2- Take a dough lump and roll it to make a round ball. 3- Roll it in the dry flour and flatten it to the diameter of 6 to 7 inches.4- Spared some Oil in it and spread it evenly. 5- Place the stuffing over it and spread it thinly. 6- Fold it in a square shape from all the sides and spared some Oil over it. 7- Roll it in the dry flour and toss the extra flour. 8- Press it using your fingers from all the corners. 9- Flatten it using a rolling pin into the shape of a square. 10- Spread some Oil on the pan and place paratha over it to fry.11- Let it roast from the bottom and flip it later on.12- Cook it until light colour spots appears on it. 13- Adds some Oil in it and spread it. 14- Flip and fry by pressing them until they are golden. 15- Remove it and place on mini bowl over a plate. 16- Prepare all the parathas in the same way and serve. description: Baba Jani - Episode 11 | HAR PAL GEOThe story revolves around the male protagonist Asfand, he is a mid-aged, well-mannered, simple and sophisticated man of character who lost his parents at an early age. Since the sad demise of his parents Asfand accepted to bear the entire responsibility of his sisters, Najiba, Naila & Nabila. Asfand‚Äôs elder sister Najiba is a cunning woman, while Naila being a middle child follow the lead. However youngest sister Nabila is a soft-hearted, young and innocent girl. Asfand was already coping up with the anomalies of life, when in a very unfavorable situation he met Sadia, an elderly aged woman with a young and beautiful daughter Nimra. Asfand proposes Sadia & offered to accept her daughter Nimra as a father with all his heart & soul. Initially Nimra dislikes Asfand but due to his kindness and sincerity she accepted him as Baba Jani. Life was never easy for Asfand, the sensitivity of his relationship with her step-daughter Nimra is not approved by the society and hence the suffering continues. Will Asfand be able to live a peaceful life with his family?
